{
  "text": "There has been a large volume of research addressing the issue of locating resources in a distributed system in a decentralized fashion (see for example [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] 9, 5] ). However, all these efforts try to locate unique data or a unique node (address) in a distributed system. The unique constant value make it difficult to apply these techniques to map resources. For example, with computing resources there is a limited number of resources, and they often have a small set of values they assume. Using a DHT (Distributed Hash Table) based approach would save all the information in a few select nodes and make them the potential bottleneck of performance.",
  "citation_candidates": [
